text: John Laichinger (March 2, 1884 - April 4, 1933) was an American gymnast. He competed in four events at the 1904 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1884 births Category:1933 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from St. Louis
